==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moebius strip
<hw>Moe"bi*us strip`</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<person>August F. <etsep>M⟦oum⟧bius</etsep></person>, a German
mathematician.]</ety> <def>A mathematical object, or a physical
representation of it, which is a two-dimensional sheet with only one
surface. It is constructed or visualized as a rectangle, one end of
which is held fixed while the opposite end is twisted through a 180
degree angle and joined to the fixed end. It is a two-dimensional object
that can only exist in a three-dimensional space.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><note>The moebius strip was the subject of a famous woodcut by
<person>M. Escher</person>, published in 1963.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moble</ent>⟦br⟧
